<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-02-28T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-02-28T12:00:00-05:00" n="169" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d169">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">560.AL/2–2748: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                                <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                            <lb/>
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                            </gloss>
                        </seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-02-28T12:00:00-05:00">February 28,
                                1948—noon</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>690. For Douglas from Clayton and Thorp. Re <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 726. Feb 25. Dept completely in accord with position
                        stated and action recommended Habana tel 249, Feb 27 repeated to London. Pls
                        proceed discussions with British officials on basis indicated last paragraph
                        Habana tel 249. We leave presentation this position to your judgment.</p>
                    <pb facs="0390" n="880" xml:id="pg_880"/>
                    <p>We are anxious that presentation be made in manner best calculated to avoid
                        antagonism and to minimize effect on our cooperation with British on other
                        issues. Sent London as 690, repeated Habana as 275. [Clayton and Thorp.]</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>